CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 21, 1965, pg. 1 reads: "Return To Commissioners - A delegation of UNPC demonstrators who had picketed at the Electrical Workers Union office and at Chatham Center, earlier in week, many of whom were arrested at both places, returned to the County Commissioners' offices in the courthouse, Tuesday afternoon, to again ask the Commissioners to hire Negro electricians. Commissioners William D. McClelland and Blair Gunther went out the front door to lunch shortly after this group arrived, about noon and sent back word that they would not return in the afternoon because they had another meeting. Commissioner John E. McGrady is at home recovering from a heart attack. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of UNPC demonstrators gathered in the County Commissioners' offices, Allegheny County Courthouse
